I"±<p>How widespread a species is, specifically with respect to other <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/organism-and-ecology-are-codetermined">species in its ecological niche</a>, might be indicative of high <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/representationism-in-cognition-is-adaptationism-in-evolution">fitness</a>. A population which mastered its environment, through <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/metabolism-influences-neural-dynamics">metabolic</a>, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memeplexes-resemble-grativational-attractors">reproductive</a>, and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/fragmentation-granularity-fosters-mixing-in-tea-and-societies">security</a> lens, is likely to be abundant in a given ecological niche. However, this <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/occam-s-razor-is-a-heuristic-for-pruning-a-solution-set">heuristic</a> is <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/categorical-perception-translates-in-a-blindspot-for-nuance">blind</a> to existential risks. Abundance should be taken into consideration together with <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/perseverence-signals-fitness">perseverence</a>.</p>
